[thinking] I need to think about the potential failures of native dynamic class loading based on existing issues. It seems metadata doesn’t include reflection. The LogFactoryImpl may use build-time class, but Class.forName might be unsupported with certain constants. The native agent might capture this. I wonder if tests generated under the agent allow for reflection configuration. It looks like the agent generates metadata for the native compile. Should I only catch for Native runtime and not for tests? That could hide failures, but if there's coverage, it might be fine.
